text: Catron County is a county in the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 3,579, making it New Mexico's third-least populous county. Its county seat is Reserve. Catron County is New Mexico's largest county by area. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:20th- century establishments in New Mexico Category:1921 establishments in the United States
